From f486c24abfcb4393e72fcf832847ea9817080f37 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chris Lu <lu@alcg.io>
Date: Fri, 20 Mar 2026 15:32:26 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 04/10] tracer: add process identification and instrument
 MON/MDS daemons

Extend Tracer::init() with service.instance.id resource attribute and
optional extra attributes to identify individual daemon processes in
traces. Add tracing infrastructure to MON (Paxos consensus, command
dispatch) and MDS (client POSIX operations) which previously had zero
OTLP instrumentation.

Process identification:
- OSD: instance.id = whoami (e.g. "0")
- RGW: instance.id = hostname:pid, extra attr rgw.zone
- MON: instance.id = mon name (e.g. "sm3")
- MDS: instance.id = hostname:pid, extra attr mds.rank

MON spans: dispatch_op, handle_command, paxos_begin, paxos_commit,
paxos_propose
MDS spans: client_request, lookup, getattr, open, readdir, mkdir,
unlink, rmdir, rename

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
